\q1
\v 41 if I \x + \xo 32:41 \xt Ps. 7:12; Isa. 27:1; 34:5; 66:16; Ezek. 21:9, 10\x*sharpen my flashing sword\f + \fr 32:41 \ft Hebrew \fq the lightning of my sword\f*
\q2 and my hand takes hold on judgment,
\q1 I will take vengeance on my adversaries
\q2 and will repay those who hate me.
\q1
\v 42 I will make my arrows drunk with blood,
\q2 and \x + \xo 32:42 \xt Jer. 46:10 \x*my sword shall devour flesh—
\q1 with the blood of the slain and the captives,
\q2 from the \x + \xo 32:42 \xt See Ps. 68:21\x*long-haired heads of the enemy.’
\b
\q1
\v 43 \x + \xo 32:43 \xt Cited Rom. 15:10 \x*“Rejoice with him, O heavens;\f + \fr 32:43 \ft Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text \fq Rejoice his people, O nations\f*
\q2 bow down to him, all gods,\f + \fr 32:43 \ft Masoretic Text lacks \fq bow down to him, all gods\f*
\q1 for he \x + \xo 32:43 \xt Rev. 6:10; 19:2; [2 Kgs. 9:7; Ps. 79:10]\x*avenges the blood of his children\f + \fr 32:43 \ft Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text \fq servants\f*
\q2 and takes vengeance on his adversaries.
\q1 He repays those who hate him\f + \fr 32:43 \ft Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text lacks \fq He repays those who hate him\f*
\q2 and cleanses\f + \fr 32:43 \ft Or \fq atones for\f* his people’s land.”\f + \fr 32:43 \ft Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew \fq his land his people\f*
\b
\p
\v 44 Moses came and recited all the words of this song in the hearing of the people, he and \x + \xo 32:44 \xt Num. 13:8, 16\x*Joshua\f + \fr 32:44 \ft Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew \fq Hoshea\f* the son of Nun.
\v 45 And when Moses had finished speaking all these words to all Israel,
\v 46 he said to them, \x + \xo 32:46 \xt ch. 11:18; See ch. 6:6 \x*“Take to heart all the words by which I am warning you today, \x + \xo 32:46 \xt See ch. 4:9\x*that you may command them to your children, that they may be careful to do all the words of this law.
\v 47 For it is no empty word for you, \x + \xo 32:47 \xt [Lev. 18:5]; See ch. 30:20\x*but your very life, and by this word you shall live long in the land that you are going over the Jordan to possess.”
\s1 Moses’ Death Foretold
\p
\v 48 That very day the \nd Lord\nd* spoke to Moses,
\v 49 “Go up \x + \xo 32:49 \xt See Num. 27:12\x*this mountain of the Abarim, Mount Nebo, which is in the land of Moab, opposite Jericho, and view the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the people of Israel for a possession.
\v 50 And die on the mountain which you go up, and be gathered to your people, as \x + \xo 32:50 \xt Num. 20:24, 25, 28; 33:38\x*Aaron your brother died in Mount Hor and was gathered to his people,
\v 51 \x + \xo 32:51 \xt Num. 20:11-13; 27:14\x*because you broke faith with me in the midst of the people of Israel at the waters of Meribah-kadesh, in the wilderness of Zin, and because you did not treat me as holy in the midst of the people of Israel.
\v 52 For \x + \xo 32:52 \xt ch. 3:27; 34:4\x*you shall see the land before you, but you shall not go there, into the land that I am giving to the people of Israel.”
\c 33
\s1 Moses’ Final Blessing on Israel
\p \v 1 This is the blessing with which Moses \x + \xo 33:1 \xt Josh. 14:6; 1 Chr. 23:14; 2 Chr. 30:16; Ezra 3:2\x*the man of God blessed the people of Israel before his death.
\v 2 He said,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 33:2 \xt [Ex. 19:18, 20; Judg. 5:4, 5; Ps. 68:7, 8; Hab. 3:3] \x*“The \nd Lord\nd* came from Sinai
\q2 and dawned from Seir upon us;\f + \fr 33:2 \ft Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew \fq them\f*
\q2 he shone forth from Mount Paran;
\q1 he came \x + \xo 33:2 \xt [Ps. 68:17; Dan. 7:10; Acts 7:53; Gal. 3:19; Heb. 2:2; Jude 14; Rev. 5:11]\x*from the ten thousands of holy ones,
\q2 with flaming fire\f + \fr 33:2 \ft The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain\f* at his right hand.
\q1
\v 3 Yes, \x + \xo 33:3 \xt ch. 7:7, 8; 10:15; Hos. 11:1 \x*he loved his people,\f + \fr 33:3 \ft Septuagint; Hebrew \fq peoples\f*
\q2 \x + \xo 33:3 \xt [John 10:27-29; Rom. 8:35, 38, 39] \x*all his holy ones were in his\f + \fr 33:3 \ft Hebrew \fq your\f* hand;
\q1 \x + \xo 33:3 \xt [Luke 10:39; Acts 22:3]\x*so they followed\f + \fr 33:3 \ft The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain\f* in your steps,
\q2 receiving direction from you,
\q1
\v 4 when \x + \xo 33:4 \xt John 1:17; 7:19\x*Moses commanded us a law,
\q2 as a possession for the assembly of Jacob.
\q1
\v 5 Thus the \nd Lord\nd*\f + \fr 33:5 \ft Hebrew \fq Thus he\f* \x + \xo 33:5 \xt Num. 23:21; [Judg. 8:23; Isa. 33:22] \x*became king in \x + \xo 33:5 \xt See ch. 32:15\x*Jeshurun,
\q2 when the heads of the people were gathered,
\q2 all the tribes of Israel together.
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 33:6 \xt [Gen. 49:3, 4]\x*“Let Reuben live, and not die,
\q2 but let his men be few.”
\b
\m
\v 7 And this he said of Judah:
\b
\q1 “Hear, O \nd Lord\nd*, the voice of Judah,
\q2 and bring him in to his people.
\q1 With your hands contend\f + \fr 33:7 \ft Probable reading; Hebrew \fq With his hands he contended\f* for him,
\q2 and be a help against his adversaries.”
\b
\m
\v 8 And \x + \xo 33:8 \xt [Gen. 49:5] \x*of Levi he said,
\b
\q1 “Give to Levi\f + \fr 33:8 \ft Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint; Masoretic Text lacks \fq Give to Levi\f* \x + \xo 33:8 \xt See Ex. 28:30 \x*your Thummim,
\q2 and your Urim to your godly one,
\q1 \x + \xo 33:8 \xt See Ex. 17:7; Num. 20:13\x*whom you tested at Massah,
\q2 with whom you quarreled at the waters of Meribah;
\q1
\v 9 who said of his father and mother,
\q2 ‘I regard them not’;
\q1 \x + \xo 33:9 \xt See Ex. 32:26-29 \x*he disowned his brothers
\q2 and ignored his children.
\q1 For \x + \xo 33:9 \xt Mal. 2:4-6\x*they observed your word
\q2 and kept your covenant.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 33:10 \xt ch. 17:9-11; Ezek. 44:23; See Lev. 10:11 \x*They shall teach Jacob your rules
\q2 and Israel your law;
\q1 \x + \xo 33:10 \xt Ex. 30:7, 8; 1 Sam. 2:28 \x*they shall put incense before you
\q2 and \x + \xo 33:10 \xt Ps. 51:19; Ezek. 43:27\x*whole burnt offerings on your altar.
\q1
\v 11 Bless, O \nd Lord\nd*, his substance,
\q2 and \x + \xo 33:11 \xt Ezek. 20:40, 41; 43:27; [Amos 5:22]\x*accept the work of his hands;
\q1 crush the loins of his adversaries,
\q2 of those who hate him, that they rise not again.”
\b
\m
\v 12 \x + \xo 33:12 \xt [Gen. 49:27]\x*Of Benjamin he said,
\b
\q1 “The beloved of the \nd Lord\nd* dwells in safety.
\q1 The High God\f + \fr 33:12 \ft Septuagint; Hebrew \fq dwells in safety by him. He\f* surrounds him all day long,
\q2 and dwells between his shoulders.”
\b
\m
\v 13 And \x + \xo 33:13 \xt [Gen. 49:22] \x*of Joseph he said,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 33:13 \xt Gen. 49:25 \x*“Blessed by the \nd Lord\nd* be his land,
\q2 with the choicest gifts of heaven \x + \xo 33:13 \xt ver. 28; Gen. 27:28\x*above,\f + \fr 33:13 \ft Two Hebrew manuscripts and Targum; Hebrew \fq with the dew\f*
\q2 and of the deep that crouches beneath,
\q1
\v 14 with the choicest fruits of the sun
\q2 and the rich yield of the months,
\q1
\v 15 with the finest produce of the ancient mountains
\q2 and the abundance of \x + \xo 33:15 \xt Gen. 49:26; Hab. 3:6; [Ps. 90:2]\x*the everlasting hills,
\q1
\v 16 with the best gifts of the earth and \x + \xo 33:16 \xt Ps. 24:1 \x*its fullness
\q2 and the favor of \x + \xo 33:16 \xt Ex. 3:2-4; Acts 7:30, 35\x*him who dwells in the bush.
\q1 May these rest on the head of Joseph,
\q2 on the pate of him who is prince among his brothers.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 33:17 \xt [1 Chr. 5:1] \x*A firstborn bull\f + \fr 33:17 \ft Dead Sea Scroll, Septuagint, Samaritan; Masoretic Text \fq His firstborn bull\f*—he has majesty,
\q2 and his horns are the horns of a \x + \xo 33:17 \xt See Num. 23:22 \x*wild ox;
\q1 with them \x + \xo 33:17 \xt 1 Kgs. 22:11; Ps. 44:5; Dan. 8:4 \x*he shall gore the peoples,
\q2 all of them, to the ends of the earth;
\q1 \x + \xo 33:17 \xt [Gen. 48:19; Num. 1:33, 35]\x*they are the ten thousands of Ephraim,
\q2 and they are the thousands of Manasseh.”
\b
\m
\v 18 And of Zebulun he said,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 33:18 \xt [Gen. 49:13-15]\x*“Rejoice, Zebulun, in your going out,
\q2 and Issachar, in your tents.
\q1
\v 19 They shall call peoples \x + \xo 33:19 \xt Ex. 15:17; Isa. 2:3 \x*to their mountain;
\q2 there they offer \x + \xo 33:19 \xt Ps. 4:5; 51:19\x*right sacrifices;
\q1 for they draw from the abundance of the seas
\q2 and the hidden treasures of the sand.”
\b
\m
\v 20 And \x + \xo 33:20 \xt [Gen. 49:19] \x*of Gad he said,
\b
\q1 “Blessed be he who enlarges Gad!
\q2 Gad crouches \x + \xo 33:20 \xt [1 Chr. 12:8]\x*like a lion;
\q2 he tears off arm and scalp.
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 33:21 \xt See Num. 32:1-5, 16-19 \x*He chose the best of the land for himself,
\q2 for there a commander’s portion was reserved;
\q1 and \x + \xo 33:21 \xt Num. 32:31, 32; See Josh. 1:12-15; 1 Chr. 5:18-22\x*he came with the heads of the people,
\q2 with Israel he executed the justice of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and his judgments for Israel.”
\b
\m
\v 22 And \x + \xo 33:22 \xt [Gen. 49:16] \x*of Dan he said,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 33:22 \xt [Gen. 49:9] \x*“Dan is a lion’s cub
\q2 \x + \xo 33:22 \xt [Josh. 19:47; Judg. 18:27]\x*that leaps from Bashan.”
\b
\m
\v 23 And \x + \xo 33:23 \xt [Gen. 49:21] \x*of Naphtali he said,
\b
\q1 “O Naphtali, sated with favor,
\q2 and full of the blessing of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 33:23 \xt See Josh. 19:32-39\x*possess the lake\f + \fr 33:23 \ft Or \fq west\f* and the south.”
\b
\m
\v 24 And \x + \xo 33:24 \xt [Gen. 49:20] \x*of Asher he said,
\b
\q1 “Most blessed of sons be Asher;
\q2 let him be the favorite of his brothers,
\q2 and let him \x + \xo 33:24 \xt [Job 29:6]\x*dip his foot in oil.
\q1
\v 25 Your bars shall be iron and bronze,
\q2 and as your days, so shall your strength be.
\b
\q1
\v 26 \x + \xo 33:26 \xt See Ex. 15:11 \x*“There is none like God, O \x + \xo 33:26 \xt See ch. 32:15 \x*Jeshurun,
\q2 \x + \xo 33:26 \xt Ps. 68:33, 34; 104:3; Isa. 19:1; Hab. 3:8\x*who rides through the heavens to your help,
\q2 through the skies in his majesty.
\q1
\v 27 The eternal God is your \x + \xo 33:27 \xt Ps. 90:1; 91:9\x*dwelling place,\f + \fr 33:27 \ft Or \fq a dwelling place\f*
\q2 and underneath are the everlasting arms.\f + \fr 33:27 \ft Revocalization of verse 27 yields \fq He subdues the ancient gods, and shatters the forces of old\f*
\q1 And he thrust out the enemy before you
\q2 and said, ‘Destroy.’
\q1
\v 28 So Israel lived in safety,
\q2 \x + \xo 33:28 \xt [Ps. 68:26; Isa. 48:1] \x*Jacob lived \x + \xo 33:28 \xt Num. 23:9\x*alone,\f + \fr 33:28 \ft Hebrew \fq the abode of Jacob was alone\f*
\q1 in a land of grain and wine,
\q2 whose heavens drop down dew.
\q1
\v 29 Happy are you, O Israel! \x + \xo 33:29 \xt [2 Sam. 7:23] \x*Who is like you,
\q2 a people \x + \xo 33:29 \xt Isa. 45:17 \x*saved by the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 \x + \xo 33:29 \xt Ps. 33:20; 115:9-11\x*the shield of your help,
\q2 and the sword of your triumph!
\q1 Your enemies shall come fawning to you,
\q2 and you shall tread upon their backs.”
\c 34
\s1 The Death of Moses
\p \v 1 Then Moses went up from the plains of Moab \x + \xo 34:1 \xt See Num. 27:12\x*to Mount Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, which is opposite Jericho. And the \nd Lord\nd* showed him all the land, Gilead as far as Dan,
\v 2 all Naphtali, the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, all the land of Judah \x + \xo 34:2 \xt See ch. 11:24\x*as far as the western sea,
\v 3 \x + \xo 34:3 \xt ch. 1:7 \x*the Negeb, and \x + \xo 34:3 \xt Gen. 13:12; 19:17, 25, 28, 29; 2 Sam. 18:23 \x*the Plain, that is, the Valley of Jericho \x + \xo 34:3 \xt Judg. 1:16; 3:13; 2 Chr. 28:15 \x*the city of palm trees, as far as \x + \xo 34:3 \xt Gen. 14:2; 19:22\x*Zoar.
\v 4 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to him, \x + \xo 34:4 \xt See Gen. 12:7; 50:24 \x*“This is the land of which I swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, ‘I will give it to your offspring.’ \x + \xo 34:4 \xt ch. 3:27; 32:52 \x*I have let you see it with your eyes, but \x + \xo 34:4 \xt See ch. 1:37\x*you shall not go over there.”
\v 5 So Moses the servant of the \nd Lord\nd* died there in the land of Moab, according to the word of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\v 6 and he buried him in the valley in the land of Moab opposite Beth-peor; but \x + \xo 34:6 \xt [Jude 9]\x*no one knows the place of his burial to this day.
\v 7 \x + \xo 34:7 \xt ch. 31:2 \x*Moses was 120 years old when he died. \x + \xo 34:7 \xt [Gen. 27:1; 48:10; Josh. 14:10, 11; 1 Sam. 3:2; 4:15]\x*His eye was undimmed, and his vigor unabated.
\v 8 And the people of Israel \x + \xo 34:8 \xt Num. 20:29; [Gen. 50:3]\x*wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty days. Then the days of weeping and mourning for Moses were ended.
\p
\v 9 And Joshua the son of Nun was full of \x + \xo 34:9 \xt Ex. 28:3; Isa. 11:2 \x*the spirit of wisdom, for \x + \xo 34:9 \xt Num. 27:18, 23 \x*Moses had laid his hands on him. So \x + \xo 34:9 \xt Josh. 1:17\x*the people of Israel obeyed him and did as the \nd Lord\nd* had commanded Moses.
\v 10 And there has not \x + \xo 34:10 \xt [ch. 18:15, 18] \x*arisen a prophet since in Israel like Moses, \x + \xo 34:10 \xt ch. 5:4; See Ex. 33:11\x*whom the \nd Lord\nd* knew face to face,
\v 11 none like him for all \x + \xo 34:11 \xt See ch. 4:34\x*the signs and the wonders that the \nd Lord\nd* sent him to do in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh and to all his servants and to all his land,
\v 12 and for all the mighty power and all the great deeds of terror that Moses did in the sight of all Israel.
